onad` instance and the number of excess state arguments. ","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/Context.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.State.frameBackwardRuleCache","kind":"def","line":176,"name":"Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.State.frameBackwardRuleCache","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/Context.lean#L176-L176"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/Context.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.State.latticeBackwardRuleCache\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">Internal</span>.<span class=\"name\">VCGen</span>.<span class=\"name\">State</span>.<span class=\"name\">latticeBackwardRuleCache</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Do/Internal/VCGen/Context.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.Do.Internal.VCGen.State\">State</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Std/Data/HashMap/Basic.html#Std.HashMap\">Std.HashMap</a> (<a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/ExprPtr.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.ExprPtr\">Meta.Sym.ExprPtr</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>) <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Sym/Apply.html#Lean.Meta.Sym.BackwardRule\">Meta.Sym.BackwardRule</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A cache mapping lattice connectives to their backward rule to apply, keyed by the `head … cₙ`\nprefix of constant arguments the rule bakes in verbatim and the total argument count that fixes the\nschematic operand and state count.\n\nThe prefix is keyed by `ExprPtr`, so lookups compare it by pointer rather than structurally. This is\nsound 